{{FUN-top|refs2=1}}
==Containers==
:''For the technical background of Trainz containers, see '''[[Trainz/AM&C/containers]]'''.<br
/>This page lists the ''''''reference pages links'''''' of specific Trainz containers covered by this Wikibook after a brief introduction of their role in the Trainz data model.''
<br>
'''Containers''' are Trainz term for complex {{Wp|data structure}}s containing more than one elemental {{wp|data type|type of data}} but data groups which might be used in more than one of Trainz {{TL|Kinds}}, in and of themselves a 'container', but of a more unique type. 

In one sense, Trainz assets are nothing but a collection of data organized by proper {{TN|E|enumerated codes}} and these containers, including the parent-classed containers known as '''{{TR|Kinds}}''' define the interrelationship and configuration of an asset, and the behavior of the digital model in the {{TN|GUI}} run-time software&mdash;the {{wp|game engine}}. The container is but one element in an assets self-definition as initialized by the asset creator.
<br>
{{TrainzTip|Recall from elementary math:
<tt>{X: A, B, C, ..., xx}</tt> is read as "The set 'X' of legal values that are one of: list of valid data values."
}}

==Data organization==
All Trainz data is represented by a key-word and a value. '''Containers''' are identified by a '''unique enumerated key-word''' (identifier) and for a container, all the values within the ''paired curly braces'' <code>'''<tt>'{' and '}'</tt>'''</code> are in the abstract, the value of the container key-word. Within, again, all elements are ''paired values'', often again a keyword and a value. 
&nbsp;

Within many containers (or in practice, a sub-container&mdash; see the form, format, and examples at {{TBS|thumbnails}} for an oft seen and easy to understand representation and example) the keyword is a de facto variable (non-enumerated and undeclared, unconstrained) and are usually ''by convention'' represented as a simple integer <tt>{X: 1, 2, 3, ..., nn}</tt> followed by whitespace and'' 'the value' ''as the right hand column in the config.txt file, which defines the data value.
&nbsp;

These are called'' 'dummy parameters' ''or '' 'dummy key-words','' or'' 'pseudo-keywords' ''and a content creator might easily instead use <tt>{X: A, B, C, ..., xx}</tt> or  <tt>{X: throttle1, throttle2, throttle3, ..., tt}</tt>, for in such cases, in all containers in fact, ''the value(s) is (are) being ordered and organized'' to fill a {{TL|KIND}} dependent  physical address in memory, normally part of an {{wp|Array data type|array}} (See {{N3V|http://online.ts2009.com/mediaWiki/index.php/Throttle-power_container#Example_throttle-power_container|throttle-power container}} or {{wp|List (abstract data type)|list}} (See the several examples in {{TR|C|thumbnails}}).

&nbsp;  
==Trainz Wikibook containers==
The Trainz Wikibook and the N3V Games TrainzOnline wiki (or Trainz Wiki) have different focus and purpose. The TrainzOnline pages are meant to be a technical specification and reference for the benefit of content creators, and a means of communication of the data needed by the run time software for an asset to operate correctly inside the {{TN|G|Trainz GUIs}}. It serves as a terse guideline to content definitions.

Here in the Trainz Wikibook our focus is on providing elementary introductory material through intermediate and some times advanced knowledge&mdash;to imparting understanding, and helping new Trainzers and old have a more verbose exposition of the ins and outs of Trainz. The costs and man-power of a small business struggling to make ends meet constrains the Trainz Wiki, which of necessity must be authoritative. We strive here for the same degree of accuracy, but also for a bigger picture and necessarily have a time lag for some changes introduced in the course of the ever ongoing evolution of Trainz. This product wouldn't have survived without such change, and while it makes it hard to 'catch up', it also makes the Trainz experience an ever improving one.
&nbsp;

When and if we deem a topic needful of additional exposition and lacking a cohesive build up of fundamental knowledge, we amplify the pages of the TrainzOnline Wiki with additional information, explanations, examples and hopefully aid understanding where the stricter terser writing is undesired by the N3V programmers who oversee the Trsinz Wiki. The following is a table of contents for our container pages to date. Below that you will see a recap of ''some key fundamental material'' in the TrainzBaseSpec.
<br>
